The main changes made to expand the main container are:

1. The `width` of the `.app` container is set to `95%` to take up most of the available width.
2. The `max-width` of the `.app` container is set to `1600px` to ensure it doesn't exceed a certain width on larger screens.
3. The `margin` of the `.app` container is set to `0 auto` to center it horizontally.
4. The `width` of the `.editor` and `.button-container` is set to `90%` to match the width of the main container.

These changes should make the main container expand to take up most of the available width while still maintaining a maximum width and centering it horizontally.

